Ask HN: Would you hire someone who memorizes the System Design Interview book?
text:
During the system design interview, my colleague gave a common question that was found in System Design interview. The candidate seems to be able to give a perfect answer (covering what the book is advising).

Objectively the candidate passed. But deep down I felt that passing the interview doesn't show me about what real life design problems that the candidate have faced before.

Ask HN: Is there a limit for individuals or small teams in the startup field?
text:
Other than software and gadgets, there doesn't seem to be any other possible field.

Can a small team, for example, start a cancer treatment or fusion power project if they study hard and work hard? If not, what would be the possible fields?

Ask HN: Should a startup block EU countries at first?
text:
I previously lived in the EU and was instrumental in bringing a 100ish employee B2B SaaS company into GDPR compliance. We weren’t in the business of disrespecting personal information, but compliance nonetheless took and continues to take a lot of time and money.

I am now outside the EU and looking to create a new B2B SaaS. It doesn’t really seem viable for a single founder to create a GDPR compliant operation.

Does it make sense to simply block all EU countries until a business has grown big enough that the benefit of access to the EU market outweighs the costs and risk?

Ask HN: How long did Stable Diffusion take to run on your home setup?
text: I ran text to image stable diffusion on a 2020 13" M1, it took 90 mins to return a single 512x512 image with the default parameters. It would be interesting to know run times that others have experienced.
